Sentencas: Y0.07Sr0.895TiO3 CYST) and La0.2Sr0.7TiO3 (LST) samples sintered and reduced at different temperatures were prepared.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs

Sentencas: The conductivity and chemical expansion of the samples were tested.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs

Sentencas: It was found that the combination of high conductivity and low chemical expansion therefore represents a conflict of material properties for YST and LST samples.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs

Sentencas: The relationship between chemical expansion and sample cracking is discussed.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs

Sentencas: The conductivity of the samples against redox cycles was also tested.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs

Sentencas: Properties with respect to SOFC requirements were compared between LST and YST samples.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs

Sentencas: Suitable preparation conditions for YST and LST as SOFC anode materials were optimized.
Titulo: Comparison of Y and La-substituted SrTiO3 as the anode materials for SOFCs
